---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Security and governance"
  description="See the repository-defined risk levels, approval rules, least-privilege principles and current pre-release security boundaries."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Governance model · Repository-defined</p><h1>
        Consequential actions remain human decisions.
      </h1><p class="lead">
        The current repository defines risk classification, approval rules and
        agent boundaries. It does not yet provide a running enforcement
        platform.
      </p><div class="demo-banner" role="note">
        <strong>Current status</strong><span
          >These are defined policies and contracts, not a claim of deployed
          security controls.</span
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Default risk policy</p><h2>
        Three levels. No ambiguous middle.
      </h2><div class="risk-grid">
        <article class="risk-card">
          <span class="risk-index">01 / Low</span><h3>Automatic</h3><p>
            Drafting, summarising, organising, planning and read-only diagnosis.
          </p><ul><li>Preparation only</li><li>Reviewable result</li></ul>
        </article><article class="risk-card">
          <span class="risk-index">02 / Medium</span><h3>Founder approval</h3><p
          >
            Publishing, community messages, website or workflow changes, and
            operational fixes.
          </p><ul>
            <li>Founder decision required</li><li>
              Conditional security review
            </li>
          </ul>
        </article><article class="risk-card">
          <span class="risk-index">03 / High</span><h3>Security + founder</h3><p
          >
            Data deletion, production, money, credentials, permissions, private
            information and commitments.
          </p><ul>
            <li>Rick review required</li><li>Explicit founder approval</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="shell split">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Fail-closed defaults</p><h2>
          Unknown means high risk.
        </h2><p class="lead">
          The policy denies actions when required approval is missing and
          requires every decision to be recorded.
        </p>
      </div><div class="code-block">
        defaults: unknownActionRisk: high denyOnMissingApproval: true
        recordDecision: true prohibited: - expand-own-permissions -
        expose-private-information - bypass-required-approval -
        conceal-material-failure
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell content-grid">
      <aside class="side-index" aria-label="Security topics">
        <a href="#least-privilege">Least privilege</a><a href="#minimum-context"
          >Minimum context</a
        ><a href="#observability">Observability</a><a href="#limitations"
          >Limitations</a
        >
      </aside><div class="prose">
        <section id="least-privilege">
          <h2>Least privilege</h2><p>
            Every agent declares its required permissions. Agents must not
            expand their own permissions, and consequential permission changes
            require security review and founder approval.
          </p>
        </section><section id="minimum-context">
          <h2>Minimum necessary context</h2><p>
            Orin selects only the context needed for a task. Private community
            information must not be exposed, and agents are not intended to
            receive unrestricted access to another agent’s raw memory.
          </p>
        </section><section id="observability">
          <h2>Reviewable decisions</h2><p>
            Important workflows, security decisions, failures and approvals are
            intended to be reviewable. Removing an extension is designed to
            preserve audit history and archive memory provenance.
          </p>
        </section><section id="limitations">
          <h2>Pre-release limitations</h2><p>
            The repository currently defines policies, schemas and intended
            behaviour. It does not yet run agents, enforce permissions at
            runtime, persist audit records, host a memory broker or deploy
            security services.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section section-dark final-cta">
    <div class="narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">Governance in context</p><h2>
        See where review and approval enter the workflow.
      </h2><div class="button-row">
        <a class="button" href="/demo">Watch the demo</a><a
          class="button button-secondary"
          href="/docs">Read source-linked docs</a
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
